# Ingestion Pipeline Fixes and Verification

I have fixed the "red lines" and execution errors in [f:\DigiQC\backend\app\ai\ingestion_pipeline.py](file:///f:/DigiQC/backend/app/ai/ingestion_pipeline.py).

## Summary of Changes

### 1. Fixed Syntax Error
A missing closing parenthesis in the [create_vector_store](file:///f:/DigiQC/backend/app/ai/ingestion_pipeline.py#72-91) function was causing a syntax error on the subsequent `print` statement.

### 2. Resolved Undefined Variable
The `embedding_model` variable was being used in the [main](file:///f:/DigiQC/backend/app/ai/ingestion_pipeline.py#92-128) function before being defined. I have now initialized it at the beginning of [main](file:///f:/DigiQC/backend/app/ai/ingestion_pipeline.py#92-128) so it's available for both loading existing stores and creating new ones.

### 3. Consolidated Duplicate Functions
There were two definitions of [create_vector_store](file:///f:/DigiQC/backend/app/ai/ingestion_pipeline.py#72-91) with conflicting signatures. I consolidated them into a single, robust function.

### 4. Updated Embedding Model
I identified that `models/embedding-001` was not available for your API key. Through diagnostic testing, I confirmed that `models/gemini-embedding-001` is the correct working model and updated the script accordingly.

## Verification Results

The script now executes successfully without errors.

```powershell
(.venv) PS F:\DigiQC\backend> python app/ai/ingestion_pipeline.py
=== RAG Document Ingestion Pipeline ===

✅ Vector store already exists. No need to re-process documents.
Loaded existing vector store with 0 documents
```

> [!NOTE]
> The "0 documents" message indicates that while the vector store exists, it hasn't indexed any documents yet. If you add [.txt](file:///f:/DigiQC/backend/test_output.txt) files to your `docs` directory and delete the `db/chroma_db` folder, the script will re-process them.

